JOHANNESBURG – Two alleged bogus doctors in Cape Town have been released on bail. Six people were arrested last week following a multi-faceted operation by the Hawks, police and the Health Professions Council of South Africa. Two of the 6 alleged bogus doctors arrested through a Hawks investigation have received five thousand rand bail each at the Khayelitsha Magistrates court. The men were arrested in a multi-faceted operation in the WC. They were allegedly operating without valid medical licenses. pic.twitter.com/G6veXaOTRL Fifteen sites were searched where these doctors allegedly operated from without valid medical licences. eNCA